      "writtenOn": "2018-04-02T16:12:14Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "i am not sure about the need for this type as an abstraction separate from its usages.\n\nit is a bit inconsistent with itself: Add() replaces \"\" to \"default\", but myMap[\"\"] does not, so a client of this type has to know about \"default\" anyway.\n\nIts Del() method is used only in one place: Notify. It seems that Notify would simpler if, instead of creating a the map, placing stuff there and then removing stuff, we had \n\n  var recipients map[string]stringset.Set\n  maybeAddRecipient :\u003d func(email, template string) {\n     if allowed(email):\n       template \u003d template or \"default\"\n        add to map\n  }\n\ninside Notify() and called it in two Notify()\u0027s loops.",
      "revId": "19ba16085d6317ba4d2b511910a0fdf5177b31d6",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
